78
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,300
Then we should use Ko on our entire body.

79
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,920
Though it's contradictory.

80
00:05:17,170 --> 00:05:18,540
Exactly.

81
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:20,940
This technique combines Ten and Ren.

82
00:05:20,940 --> 00:05:22,290
Ken.

83
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:24,470
Ken

84
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,310
You defend yourself

85
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:27,920
by shrouding your body in
much more aura than usual.

86
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:32,850
It isn't as strong as Ko,
but it's far more practical.

87
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:35,930
Gon, use Ren.

88
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:40,440
To sustain that for a prolonged
period is called Ken.

89
00:05:41,570 --> 00:05:44,080
Now protect yourself from my punch!

90
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,810
So slow.

91
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:06,090
You must have relaxed when you
saw how slowly I was moving.

92
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:09,530
If you'd stopped using Ken,
your face would have been smashed.

93
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:12,310
That was the power of Ko alone.

94
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:16,860
When I add the speed and power
packed by a normal punch,

95
00:06:16,860 --> 00:06:19,100
it becomes many times stronger.

96
00:06:19,590 --> 00:06:21,230
Even dozens of times stronger.

97
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:27,990
I'll start by going slowly,
but you won't get any warning.

98
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:32,620
Keep using Ken, and try to
withstand my attacks.

99
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,520
Gon!

100
