00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,090
Good job, Killua.

177
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:46,950
Same to you.

178
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:49,040
Then, let's get started.

179
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:49,960
Osu!

180
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:52,960
Today, we'll be training in
the Enhancer category.

181
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,840
Level 1 is smashing rocks.

182
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,220
Crush them like this.

183
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:03,720
Smash a thousand with a single stone
in a day, and you clear the level.

184
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:05,590
And begin!

185
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:15,030
This is pretty tough.

186
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:17,170
All I'm doing is

187
00:11:17,170 --> 00:11:20,740
changing the stone to 100 POW
at the moment of impact.

188
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:24,740
But my Nen is weakening as I go.

189
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:27,500
Oops, it crumbled...

190
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,720
If the stone in your hand breaks, it's over.

191
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,000
Damn!

192
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,630
Damn, I failed!

193
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:37,880
What are you talking about?
You did well.

194
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:39,460
Okay!

195
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:42,190
Let's do Transmuter training next.

196
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:44,490
Now, now, don't rush.

197
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:48,140
You're only allowed to train
one category per day.

198
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:49,480
6!

199
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,390
Bingo! A draw.

200
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,050
Again?

201
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:54,970
These days, we keep getting draws.

202
00:11:54,970 --> 00:11:58,650
That just shows that you've both
grown accustomed to using Gyo.

203
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,670
But if there's no winner, it's no fun.

204
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:04,160
Okay, then we'll decide
with rock-paper-scissors.

205
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:07,240
The loser does a thousand push-ups!

206
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,700
Sure.

207
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:10,480
First comes rock...

208
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,150
Rock, paper, scissors!

209
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,620
One more time!

210
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:15,590
I win!

211
00:12:15,590 --> 00:12:16,650
Damn!

212
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:17,940
Hey, boys...

213
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:21,180
Have you heard the theory that
rock-paper-scissors began in martial arts?

214
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:21,670
Huh?

215
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:27,620
Palm

216
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:28,020
Paper represents a palm attack that
wrecks the opponent's organs.

217
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,640
Fingers

218
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:30,600
Scissors represents a finger jab,
targeting vital points.

219
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:34,690
Fist

220
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:34,410
And rock represents a punch with
the fist to deal external damage.

221
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:48,870
Evil Fist

222
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:39,470
Long ago, when martial arts were mistaken

223
00:12:39,470 --> 00:12:43,890
as purely destructive and banned as an evil art,

224
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:47,880
martial artists trained by playing this game.

225
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:53,570
And that's how rock-paper-scissors came to be.

226
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:55,960
You really are old...

227
00:12:58,640 --> 00:12:59,460
That's it!

228
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:01,080
Eh?

229
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:04,140
Evil Fist.

230
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:10,020
Now, everyone.

231
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:15,480
We have a total of 133 cards from
90 of the 100 total restricted slot cards.

232
00:13:15,690 --> 00:13:17,660
This is the product of your hard work.

233
00:13:17,660 --> 00:13:18,730
You have our thanks.

234
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:23,460
Of the remaining 10 cards, we've located 7.

235
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:25,930
They're as good as ours.

236
00:13:26,690 --> 00:13:30,080
However, Tsezgerra's group has also obtained

237
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:33,010
an equal number of restricted slot cards.

238
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:37,790
The final hurdle will likely be a
showdown against their group.

239
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:43,130
But I believe we have more,
and better, spell cards!

240
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:46,630
Gentlemen, our victory is near!

241
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:51,840
Can I say something?

242
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:57,020
These five years have been
so long, yet so short...

243
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:02,520
There's something I must tell you.

244
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:06,030
I am the Bomber.

245
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,050
What? The Bomber?

246
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,410
H-Hey, what are you talking about?

247
00:14:15,410 --> 00:14:16,910
Now, now... Hear me out.

248
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:20,670
I've placed bombs on all of you.

249
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:22,670
What was that?

250
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:24,420
How did you do that?!

251
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,050
Don't mess with us!

252
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,800
Stay calm and listen.

253
00:14:37,150 --> 00:14:38,470
Good grief.

254
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:41,690
You ruined the explanation I'd planned.

255
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,410
This is my power...

256
00:14:44,410 --> 00:14:46,210
Little Flower.

257
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,440
Fistful of Gunpowder
Little Flower

258
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:47,980
As you just saw,

259
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:50,440
I can blow up anything I grab with my hand.

260
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:52,950
But it isn't very strong.

261
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,050
He's still alive.

262
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:56,950
However,

263
00:14:57,260 --> 00:15:00,460
if the bombs on your bodies explode,

264
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,090
you will die.

265
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:08,210
A bomb? Where is it?

266
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:12,470
I will now tell you how to disarm the bombs.

267
00:15:13,690 --> 00:15:16,770
Let's start with how I set them.

268
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:20,270
That was by touching the place on
the target I wanted to explode,

269
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:23,350
and saying a certain keyword.

270
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:24,480
The keyword is

271
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:26,730
"Bomber."

272
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,560
It was the Bomber again.

273
00:15:35,550 --> 00:15:38,230
Listen... Beware of the Bomber.

274
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,230
In order to disarm the bombs,

275
00:15:41,230 --> 00:15:45,890
you must touch my body and say,
"I caught the Bomber."

276
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:50,760
However, I also have the Little Flower ability.

277
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:54,890
I can use this to stop anyone
who tries to touch me.

278
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:59,030
You must be very careful as you
attempt to disarm the bombs.

279
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:00,410
That's all.

280
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:09,670
They're armed.

281
00:16:10,350 --> 00:16:13,150
This is the ability Countdown.

282
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:14,530
Sound of Life
Countdown

283
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:19,540
Why am I telling you so
much about my powers?

284
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:23,040
That's the condition for arming the bombs.

285
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:26,880
Then you've been waiting for
the day when all the cards

286
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,550
and members were gathered.

287
00:16:28,910 --> 00:16:31,290
Now, I have a proposition.

288
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:36,550
I will trade your lives for those
90 restricted slot cards.

289
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:41,520
If you agree, I will use an alternative method,

290
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:44,940
and simultaneously disarm all the bombs.

291
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:50,390
Do nothing, and all of you will die
when the counter reaches zero.

292
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:53,700
You should discuss this amongst yourselves.

293
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:57,520
I'll be waiting for you at
Mr. Battera's old mansion.

294
00:16:58,230 --> 00:17:00,570
I don't care who comes, but come alone.

295
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:03,710
Are you insane?

296
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:08,660
If we just catch you now and
disarm the bombs, it's all over.

297
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:12,160
Do you think you can escape alone?!

298
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,410
Calm yourselves...

299
00:17:13,810 --> 00:17:16,530
If you get too excited,
the countdown will accelerate.

300
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:20,710
Because the counter is linked
to your heartbeat.

301
00:17:20,710 --> 00:17:21,350
What?

302
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:23,430
Book!

303
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:25,880
Crap!

304
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:30,610
I pray we meet again!

305
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,110
Leave
Send one target player
off the island.
[SR][NORM]

306
00:17:31,070 --> 00:17:32,110
Leave on!

307
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,030
He escaped outside the game!

308
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:37,870
We have to follow him...

309
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,060
Wait!

310
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:42,180
If we leave, the cards inside
our binders will vanish!

311
00:17:42,180 --> 00:17:43,500
Then what do we do?

312
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,280
Calm down!

313
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:47,500
It would be unwise to chase him down!

314
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:51,230
Have you forgotten why we teamed up?

315
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:53,510
Because we aren't strong fighters!

316
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:57,900
Does anyone here think they're
strong enough to defeat him?

317
00:17:58,460 --> 00:17:59,600
It would be impossible.

318
00:18:00,450 --> 00:18:04,020
Given his Nen abilities, he must be powerful.

319
00:18:04,830 --> 00:18:08,660
If all of us attacked him together,

320
00:18:08,660 --> 00:18:11,020
he could use Little Flower to defeat us all.

321
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,280
Damn, we were so close!

322
00:18:14,670 --> 00:18:18,230
First, we must reach a consensus.

323
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:19,800
Do we hand over the cards?

324
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,610
Or do we fight?

325
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,410
Please give him the cards...

326
00:18:24,660 --> 00:18:25,620
I beg you.

327
00:18:28,260 --> 00:18:31,000
Jispa's running out of time...

328
00:18:38,220 --> 00:18:39,430
That's a surprise.

329
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,870
I was expecting Nickes to come.

330
00:18:42,870 --> 00:18:44,340
I'm surprised, too.

331
00:18:44,340 --> 00:18:46,060
I didn't expect you to be alone...

332
00:18:47,970 --> 00:18:49,260
Sub and Bara.

333
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:51,310
They're the other bombers.

334
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:54,320
Now give me your ring.

335
00:18:56,130 --> 00:18:57,180
What's wrong?

336
00:18:58,140 --> 00:18:59,870
I can't turn it over yet...

337
00:19:00,530 --> 00:19:03,430
Actually, we still haven't reached a decision.

338
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:09,630
And Nickes has requested the Breath
of Archangel card to save Jispa.

339
00:19:09,630 --> 00:19:10,800
Screw that!

340
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,820
As it stands, neither side can win this!

341
00:19:12,820 --> 00:19:13,590
Eh?

342
00:19:13,940 --> 00:19:17,320
You don't realize how hysterical they are.

343
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:21,000
If they can't make a decision before
time expires and they explode,

344
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,970
you'll lose the data in their rings!

345
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:24,550
But I can—

346
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:27,470
But you can convince them?

347
00:19:28,850 --> 00:19:31,140
Are you trying to bargain with me?

348
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,240
When striking a bargain,

349
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:39,490
you have to demonstrate just
how calm and insane you are.

350
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:41,140
W-Wait...

351
00:19:41,140 --> 00:19:41,990
If you kill me...

352
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,580
Don't worry.

353
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:51,140
If you kill a player outside the
game and take their ring,

354
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:54,130
the restricted slot data will not vanish.

355
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,130
Well, I doubt you have any of the cards.

356
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:12,680
A gift.

357
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:16,670
Puhat!

358
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:18,400
You won't get another chance.

359
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,490
Okay?

360
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:20,780
Leave...

361
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:24,310
The spell card! Leave!

362
00:20:25,030 --> 00:20:26,490
I need to exit, so give it to me.

363
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:28,160
Hell, no!

364
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,110
Leave is a valuable card.

365
00:20:30,110 --> 00:20:31,500
We can't waste any!

366
00:20:31,890 --> 00:20:33,990
Okay, then...

367
00:20:33,990 --> 00:20:35,650
If I don't return,

368
00:20:35,650 --> 00:20:38,810
it won't be possible to disarm all
your bombs simultaneously.

369
00:20:38,810 --> 00:20:39,510
What?

370
00:20:40,450 --> 00:20:42,760
I'm also a bomber.

371
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:46,540
There are three of us.

372
00:20:46,540 --> 00:20:48,690
Well, Genthru's the main one,

373
00:20:48,690 --> 00:20:50,770
and we're just extras.

374
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:55,460
When the three of us join our
right thumbs and say the keyword,

375
00:20:55,460 --> 00:20:57,160
the bombs will be destroyed.

376
00:20:57,660 --> 00:21:00,280
That's the alternative method.

377
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,560
Whatever...

378
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,490
I'll take my time returning
via normal means.

379
00:21:05,490 --> 00:21:07,570
You guys will be dead soon.

380
00:21:07,570 --> 00:21:09,280
Wait! Hold on!

381
00:21:11,130 --> 00:21:12,880
Please use this.

382
00:21:16,490 --> 00:21:18,540
You should have done that
in the first place, scum!

383
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,990
We'll need Leave cards
when the deal is made.

384
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,420
Have three ready.

385
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,050
Got it?

386
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:35,290
Twelve hours before Genthru
revealed himself as the Bomber,

387
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:41,030
a single boat attempted to
invade from the outside.

388
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:45,490
So it does exist in the real world.

389
00:21:47,130 --> 00:21:50,330
That's gotta be Greed Island.

390
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:07,470
G.I. Tutorial

391
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:05,120
Coming up, it's the
Greed Island Tutorial!

392
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,360
Today, we introduce the card Leave.

393
00:23:07,510 --> 00:23:19,040
Leave
Send one target player
off the island.
[SR][NORM]

394
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:11,960
This takes us back to the real world?

395
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,080
That's nice.

396
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:16,050
If you're going out, leave the free slot cards.

397
00:23:16,050 --> 00:23:17,640
Stupid onliner!

398
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,690
Huh?

399
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:21,250
Continue!

400
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:28,260
Next time: Evil Fist x And x Rock-Paper-Scissors.

401
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:30,300
See ya here next week!

402
